ured error with all three attempts and their test results","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Pure control flow and data collection logic. Real failures: loop doesn't stop after attempt 3, attempt data is lost mid-loop, error structure is missing fields. These are logic failures independent of LLM or test correctness. Integration test with mocked LLM/test runner that fails predictably allows verification of loop termination and complete attempt collection.","test_description":"Mock the LLM to always return invalid code ('syntax error'). Run the service end-to-end. Verify: (1) exactly 3 LLM calls are made, no 4th attempt, (2) returned error object contains an 'attempts' list with 3 entries, (3) each entry has required fields: attempt_number, generated_code, test_output, error_message, (4) error.attempts[2].test_output matches the final test execution.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Could unit-test the counter logic in isolation, but that misses failures in the loop's data collection and early exit. Integration level catches the full control flow.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full loop—generate, test, refine, test again—produces a working implementation for a function that a single LLM call typically gets wrong","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Explicitly tests 'full loop' and end-to-end refinement. 'Function that a single LLM call typically gets wrong' means only the real LLM fails, receives feedback, and improves—mocking destroys this. Real failure: refinement doesn't help; code never passes despite multiple attempts. Requires real LLM non-determinism (may fail attempt 1, succeed attempt 2), real error messages, and multiple agentic steps in sequence.","test_description":"Select a function known to require multi-step refinement (e.g., recursive algorithm with off-by-one errors, or complex state machine). Run the full service with real LLM and real test suite. Verify final code passes all tests. Run the test 5+ times to ensure success is not a fluke—each run will have different LLM behavior and refinement paths, and all should eventually succeed (or all fail consistently if refinement is broken).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Single Agentic test (one LLM call) can't test refinement. Mocked Integration test defeats the purpose—mocks always succeed/fail predictably, hiding real refinement dynamics. Workflow level is essential.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.75}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13491,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13491},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"85eb15b6-d292-4441-870a-57d8703bb08f","uuid":"1e006740-a39b-4c7e-8fe7-4bb8ba2a641f"}
